@page "/rules"

<PageTitle>Rules - Madtorio</PageTitle>

<h1>Community Rules & Guidelines</h1>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h2>Core Principles</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>
            Our community is built on respect, collaboration, and a shared love of Factorio.
            These rules help ensure everyone has a positive experience.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h2>General Rules</h2>
            </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Be Respectful:</strong> Treat all community members with respect. No harassment,
                hate speech, or personal attacks will be tolerated.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Stay On Topic:</strong> Keep discussions related to Factorio and factory building.
                Off-topic conversations should be kept to designated channels.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>No Cheating or Exploits:</strong> When sharing save files or discussing gameplay,
                avoid promoting exploits that break the intended game mechanics.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Give Credit:</strong> If you're sharing someone else's design or build, always
                give proper credit to the original creator.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Constructive Criticism:</strong> Feedback is welcome, but keep it constructive
                and helpful. Focus on the design, not the designer.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h2>Discord Server Rules</h2>
            </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Follow Discord TOS:</strong> All Discord Terms of Service and Community Guidelines apply.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Use Appropriate Channels:</strong> Post content in the correct channels to keep
                discussions organized.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>No Spam:</strong> Avoid excessive messages, emoji spam, or repeatedly posting
                the same content.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Respect Moderators:</strong> Follow moderator instructions. If you have concerns
                about moderation, discuss them privately.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h2>Save File Guidelines</h2>
            </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Appropriate Content:</strong> Save files must be appropriate for all audiences.
                No offensive names, chat messages, or inappropriate blueprints.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Accurate Descriptions:</strong> Provide clear, accurate descriptions of your
                save files to help others understand what they're downloading.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>File Size:</strong> Keep save files under 500MB when possible. Larger files
                take longer to download.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Working Saves:</strong> Only upload save files that are functional and loadable.
                Test before uploading.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h2>Consequences</h2>
            </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>
            Rule violations may result in warnings, temporary mutes, or permanent bans depending on severity.
            Repeated violations will result in escalating consequences.
        </p>
        <p>
            Moderators have final say in rule enforcement and may take action for behaviors not explicitly
            listed if they negatively impact the community.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h2>Questions?</h2>
            </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>
            If you have questions about these rules or need clarification, please reach out to a moderator
            on our Discord server.
        </p>
        <a href="https://tinyurl.com/madtorio-server" target="_blank" class="btn">
            Join Discord
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
    </div>
</div>

<footer class="mt-5">
    <p>Thank you for being part of the Madtorio community!</p>
</footer>
